'''collectd-web''' is a web-based perl CGI front-end for RRD data collected by [[collectd]].

== Installation ==
{{Emerge|www-apps/collectd}}

== Configuration ==
{{File|/etc/collectd/collection.conf|Define data dir where to look for rrd files|<pre>
datadir: "/var/lib/collectd"
# ^ default location
</pre>}}

== Execution ==
After installation you will end up with most of the collectd-web on your filesystem but no way to run it.

The simplest way to run is just

{{RootCmd|cd /usr/share/webapps/collectd-web/<version>/hostroot/
|chown +x cgi-bin -R
|wget https://raw.github.com/httpdss/collectd-web/0.4.1/runserver.py
|python2 runserver <ip> <port>}}

Now you can just point your browser at <ip>:<port> and you're done.

